{"parse":{"title":"g","pageid":8692,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Appendix:Variations of \"g\"|ց|ɡ|uni=auto}}\n{{character info}}\n{{character info/var|ᵍ|ｇ}}\n{{character image|IPA Unicode 0x0261.svg|caption=Some typefaces have an open-tail form of ''g''. This has a dedicated Unicode character {{angbr IPA|[[ɡ]]}} for [[International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]] use.}}\n{{minitoc}}\n==Translingual==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|mul|Voiced velar stop.ogg|Pronunciation of {{IPAchar|[ɡɑː ɑɡɡɑː]}} with the sound {{IPAchar|[ɡ]}}}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Letter====\n{{mul-letter|upper=G|lower=g|sc=Latn}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|mul|letter|7}}\n\n=====See also=====\n{{Latn-script}}\n* {{qualifier|IPA}}: [[ɡ]]\n* Greek forms: [[Γ]], [[γ]]\n* Guitar Chord - ''G'' - Played 3 3 0 0 2 3\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{ety|mul|id=gram|:abbrev|en:gram|tree=1|text=+}}\n\n====Symbol====\n{{mul-symbol}}\n\n# {{senseid|mul|Q41803}} Symbol for the [[gram#English:_Q41803|gram]], an [[Appendix:SI units|SI unit]] of [[mass]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|termlang=mul|year=2013|title=Physics of Societal Issues: Calculations on National Security, Environment, and Energy|author=David Hafemeister|publisher=Springer|isbn=9781461492726|page=23|passage=A more useable size might be 1 '''g''' with an accelerated decay of 200 kg of TNT. The isomer bomb obtained funding, but was canceled as nonsensical.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|termlang=mul|author=Kate Connolly|title=Germany legalises possession of cannabis for personal use|magazine=w:The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2024/feb/23/germany-on-track-to-partly-legalise-cannabis-for-personal-use-after-heated-debate|date=23-02-2024|passage=The law passed by the chancellor, Olaf Scholz’s ruling three-party coalition, legalises cultivating up to three plants for private consumption, the possession of 50'''g''' of cannabis at one time at home, and 25'''g''' in public.|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240401170359/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2024/feb/23/germany-on-track-to-partly-legalise-cannabis-for-personal-use-after-heated-debate}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|gram symbol}}\n* Armenian: {{t|hy|գ}}\n* Greek: {{t|el|γρ}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|г}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\n{{ety|mul|id=gravity|:abbrev|en:gravity|tree=1|text=+}}\n\n====Symbol====\n{{mul-symbol}}\n\n# Symbol for gravitational [[acceleration]] (by [[gravity#English:_Q11412|gravity]]), approximately 9.81 m/s<sup>2</sup> or 32 ft/sec<sup>2</sup> at the earth's surface. Distinguished from [[G#Translingual:_Q18373|G]].\n\n===Etymology 4===\n{{ety|mul|id=gluon|:abbrev|en:gluon|tree=1|text=+}}\n\n====Symbol====\n{{mul-symbol}}\n\n# {{lb|mul|particle}} [[gluon]]\n\n===Etymology 5===\n\n====Symbol====\n{{mul-symbol}}\n\n# {{lb|mul|IPA}} {{alternative form of|mul|ɡ<qq:[[voiced]] [[velar]] [[stop]]>}}\n# {{lb|mul|superscript {{angbr IPA|ᵍ}}|IPA}} {{alternative form of|mul|ᶢ}}\n# {{lb|mul|superscript {{angbr IPA|ᵍ}}|NAPA}} {{non-gloss|Forms digraphs for the doubly articulated consonants {{angbr IPA|ᵍb}} and {{angbr IPA|ᵍɓ}}.}}\n\n===Gallery===\n<gallery caption=\"Letter styles\" perrow=3 mode=packed>\nImage:Latin G.png|Uppercase and lowercase versions of '''G''', in normal and italic type\nImage:Fraktur letter g.svg|Uppercase and lowercase '''G''' in [[Fraktur]]\n</gallery>\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|mul|Ȝ}}\n* {{l|mul|Ŋ}}\n{{Letter\n|page=G\n|NATO=Golf\n|Morse=––·\n|Braille=⠛\n}}\n\n[[Category:IPA symbols|G]]\n[[Category:Symbols for SI units]]\n\n==English==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{sense|letter name}} {{IPA|en|/d͡ʒiː/}}\n: {{audio|en|en-us-g.ogg|a=US}}\n: {{audio|en|en-uk-g.ogg|a=UK}}\n* {{homophones|en|gee}}\n* {{rhymes|en|q=letter name|iː|s=1}}\n* {{sense|phoneme}} {{IPA|en|/ɡ/|/d͡ʒ/}}\n\n====Letter====\n{{letter|en}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|en|letter|7|gee}}\n\n=====See also=====\n{{list:Latin script letters/en}}\n\n====Number====\n{{numeral symbol|en}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|en|ordinal|7|gee}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nAbbreviations.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{lb|en|physics}} A unit of [[gravitational]] [[acceleration]].\n#: {{alti|en|G}}\n#: {{coi|en|[[pull Gs|pull '''Gs''']]}}\n# {{abbreviation of|en|gram}}.\n# {{lb|en|chiefly|US}} {{abbreviation of|en|grand|t=[[thousand]] ([[dollar]]s, [[pound]]s etc.)}}.\n#: {{alti|en|G}}\n# {{lb|en|text messaging|slang}} {{abbr of|en|good}}.\n#: {{ux|en|All '''g''', it happens.}}\n# {{lb|en|AAVE}} {{abbr of|en|gangster}}.\n# {{lb|en|Internet slang}} {{abbreviation of|en|grin|addl=; often enclosed in {{m|mul|:* *}} or {{m|mul|{{unsupported|< >}}}} to indicate that the user is grinning}}.\n#: {{cot|en|bg|t1=big grin|vbg|t2=very big grin}}\n#* {{quote-newsgroup|en|date=May 12 2007|author=FastWolf|title=Re: Re: i like paris hilton (off topic, am i ever on topic?)|url=https://groups.google.com/d/msg/alt.drugs.hard/vD6Q0f7g4LA/mcywXO_tpN0J\n|id=ft2d43t7k9injhqvlhfssg5c8n89eejim3@4ax.com|newsgroup=alt.drugs.hard|passage=Call me old fashioned, but the cyberdong virtual dildo just didn't do it for me. {{...}} PS= Does that make the cyberdong a dildon't? ... okay I apologize <'''g'''>}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col4|en|hard g|soft g|get one's a into g|g-word|g-girl|g-force|g-factor|g value|anti-g|g st|zero-g|''g''-dropping|it's all g|g-block}}\n\n==Azerbaijani==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{qualifier|phoneme}} {{IPA|az|[ɟ]|[ɟʝ]}} \n* {{qualifier|letter name}} {{IPA|az|[ɟeː]|[ɟɯː]|[ɟʝeː]|[ɟʝɯː]}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|az}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|az|letter|9}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/az}}\n\n==Basque==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{eu-IPA|ge}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|eu}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|eu|letter|7|ge}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/eu}}\n\n==Catalan==\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|ca}}\n\n# {{gl|used to represent {{IPAchar|/ɡ/}} before ''a'', ''o'' or ''u''; {{IPAchar|/ʒ/}} ({{IPAchar|/d͡ʒ/}} in Valencian) before ''e'' or ''i''; {{IPAchar|/t͡ʃ/}} at the end of a syllable after ''i'' (assimilating to {{IPAchar|/d͡ʒ/}} before a voiced consonant); and {{IPAchar|/k/}} at the end of a word}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/ca}}\n\n==Central Mazahua==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|maz|/ɡ/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|maz}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|maz|letter}}\n\n====See also====\n{{Latn-script}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/maz}}\n\n==Chipewyan==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|chp|/k/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|chp}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|chp|letter}}\n\n==Czech==\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|cs}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|cs|letter|12}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* Used only in loanwords.\n\n===See also===\n{{list:Latin script letters/cs}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-g.ogg}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|eː|s=1}}\n* {{sense|letter name}} {{IPA|nl|/ɣeː/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{letter|nl}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|nl|letter|7}}\n# {{lb|nl|physics}} a unit of gravitational acceleration\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|nl\n|g-sleutel\n|harde g\n|zachte g\n}}\n\n====See also====\n* Previous letter: {{l|nl|f}}\n* Next letter: {{l|nl|h}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|nl|noun}}\n\n# {{lb|nl|physics}} {{abbr of|nl|gram}}\n\n==Esperanto==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{q|phoneme}} {{eo-pr|#,k<q:before a voiceless consonant>}}\n{{q|letter}} {{eo-pr|'go|r=-|s=-|a=LL-Q143 (epo)-Lepticed7-go.wav;LL-Q143 (epo)-Robin van der Vliet-go.wav}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|eo}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|eo|letter|8|go}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/eo}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:eo:PIV 2020}}\n* {{R:eo:ReVo|go}}\n\n==Estonian==\n{{wp|et:}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{et-IPA|gee}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|et}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|et|letter|7|gee}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/et}}\n\n==Faroese==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|fo|/k/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|fo}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|fo|letter|8}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/fo}}\n\n==Finnish==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymid|fi|letter}}\n{{fi-ety-letter}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{s|sound}} {{IPA|fi|/ɡ/}} {{q|generally, except in {{orth|ng}}}}\n{{fi-pronunciation|gee|q1=name of letter|a=Fi-g.ogg|ac=Audio: {{m|fi|gee}}, {{m|fi|kengät}}, {{m|fi|grilli}}, {{m|fi|gee}}}}\n\n====Letter====\n{{letter|fi}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|fi|letter|7|gee}}\n\n=====Usage notes=====\n* Used only in loanwords except for {{orth|ng}} {{IPAchar|[ŋː]}}.\n\n=====See also=====\n{{list:Latin script letters/fi}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{etymid|fi|note}}\n[[w:Musical note#Note names and their history|German musical notation]].\n\n====Noun====\n{{fi-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|fi|music}} [[G]] {{gloss|note}}\n\n=====Usage notes=====\n{{U:fi:note capitalization}}\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{fi-decl-maa-dot|g|e|ä}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|fi|title=compounds\n|G-duuri\n|g-molli\n}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|gé}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Jules78120-g.wav}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-WikiLucas00-g.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-LoquaxFR-g.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|fr}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|fr|letter|7}}\n\n===Symbol===\n{{head|fr|symbol}}\n\n# {{lb|fr|physics}} {{l|en|g}}\n# {{lb|fr|texting|_|slang}} {{abbr of|fr|j'ai||I have}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|'''g''' pas dfric|i don't have any cash}}\n\n==Fula==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ff|/ɡ/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|ff}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|ff|letter}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* {{U:ff:common}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/ff}}\n\n==Ghomara==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|gho|ga<ll:when used with a pronoun>}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{inh+|gho|ber-pro|-}}. Cognate with {{cog|shi|ɣ}} and {{cog|rif|di}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{gho-IPA}}\n\n===Preposition===\n{{gho-preposition}}\n\n# [[in]]\n#: {{uxa|gho|Yat teqqim '''g''' uxyam i juj rewlen.|One stayed '''in''' the house and two fled.}}\n\n====Usage notes====\nNouns following this preposition are placed in the {{lg|annexed state}}.\n\n===References===\n* {{R:gho:Mourigh:2015}}\n\n==Gothic==\n\n===Romanization===\n{{got-rom}}\n\n# {{romanization of|got|𐌲}}\n\n==Heiltsuk==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|hei|/c/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|hei}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|hei|letter}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/hei}}\n\n==Hungarian==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{sense|phoneme}} {{hu-IPA}}\n* {{sense|letter name}} {{hu-IPA|gé}}\n* {{audio|hu|Hu-gé.ogg}}\n\n====Letter====\n{{letter|hu}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|hu|letter|12|gé}}\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{hu-infl-nom|g-|e}}{{hu-pos-tek|g-}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|hu|g-moll}}\n\n=====See also=====\n{{list:Latin script letters/hu}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{abbrev|hu|gramm||gram}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{hu-noun|-ok}}\n\n# {{l|en|g}} {{gloss|a unit of [[mass]] equal to one-thousandth of a [[kilogram]]}}\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{hu-infl-nom|g-o|o|v=m}}{{hu-pos-otok|g-|j|jai}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:ErtSz|1|sound, letter, and abbreviation}}\n* {{R:ErtSz|2|musical note and its key}}\n\n{{cln|hu|terms with multiple lemma etymologies|terms with letter and noun etymologies}}\n\n==Icelandic==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|is|/cɛː/|a=letter name}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|is}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|is|letter|9}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/is}}\n\n==Ido==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|io|/ɡ/|a=context pronunciation}}\n* {{IPA|io|/ɡe/|a=letter name}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|io}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|io|letter|7}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/io}}\n\n==Indonesian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{sense|letter name}} {{IPA|id|/ɡe/}}\n* {{sense|phoneme}} {{IPA|id|/ɡ/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|id}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|id|letter|7}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/id}}\n\n===Adverb===\n{{head|id|adverb}}\n\n# {{lb|id|texting}} {{abbreviation of|id|gak|t=no}}\n#: {{ux|id|gw '''g''' tau|i '''don't''' know}}\n\n==Interlingua==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{sense|letter name}} {{IPA|ia|/dʒe/}}\n* {{sense|phoneme}} {{IPA|ia|/dʒ/}} before 'i'/'e'/'y', as {{IPAchar|/ʒ/}} in the suffix ''-age'', and {{IPAchar|/ɡ/}} elsewhere.\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|ia}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|ia|letter|7}}\n\n====See also====\n* Previous letter: [[f]]\n* Next letter: [[h]]\n\n==Irish==\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|ga}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|ga|letter|7|{{l|ga|gé|id=G}}}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/ga}}\n\n==Isoko==\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|iso}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|iso|letter|9}}\n\n===References===\n* E. O. Agbada et al, ''Vbuhrẹ Ụmụ́bọrá Isoko (Teach Yourself Isoko), first published 2008, revised edition 2017,'' page 8, 10\n* Onyerioma Isaac Itegolor, ''Isoko Wha Dooo...! Book 2 (Operation Speak Your Language), Revised Standard Edition (2015)'', page 1\n* Joe Okedi, ''Abidi Isoko Na Kpobi'', 2020\n\n==Italian==\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|it}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|it|letter|7|gi}}\n\n==Japanese==\n{{ja-see|グラム}}\n\n==Kankanaey==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|kne|tl|g}}. Letter pronunciation is influenced by {{der|kne|en|g}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{kne-pr|dyi<a:letter name>|g<a:phoneme>}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{kne-head|letter}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|kne|letter|7|dyi}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/kne}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:kne:Ortograpiya 2016|page=10-11}}\n\n==Kashubian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{csb-ety-letter}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|csb}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|csb|letter|11|}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/csb}}\n\n==Latin==\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|la}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|la|letter|addl=representing the sound /g/}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/la}}\n\n==Latvian==\n{{wp|lv:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nProposed in 1908 as part of the new Latvian spelling by the scientific commission headed by [[w:Kārlis Mīlenbahs|K. Mīlenbahs]], which was accepted and began to be taught in schools in 1909. Prior to that, Latvian had been written in German [[Fraktur]], and sporadically in [[Cyrillic]].\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{lv-IPA|ɡ}}\n* {{audio|lv|lv-riga-g.ogg}}\n\n===Letter===\n[[File:Latin alphabet Gg.svg|thumb|200px|G]]\n{{letter|lv}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|lv|letter|10|gā}}\n\n====See also====\n* ''Letters of the Latvian alphabet:''\n*: '''{{l|lv|burts|burti}}:''' {{l|lv|A}}{{l|lv|a}}, {{l|lv|Ā}}{{l|lv|ā}}, {{l|lv|B}}{{l|lv|b}}, {{l|lv|C}}{{l|lv|c}}, {{l|lv|Č}}{{l|lv|č}}, {{l|lv|D}}{{l|lv|d}}, {{l|lv|E}}{{l|lv|e}}, {{l|lv|Ē}}{{l|lv|ē}}, {{l|lv|F}}{{l|lv|f}}, {{l|lv|G}}{{l|lv|g}}, {{l|lv|Ģ}}{{l|lv|ģ}}, {{l|lv|H}}{{l|lv|h}}, {{l|lv|I}}{{l|lv|i}}, {{l|lv|Ī}}{{l|lv|ī}}, {{l|lv|J}}{{l|lv|j}}, {{l|lv|K}}{{l|lv|k}}, {{l|lv|Ķ}}{{l|lv|ķ}}, {{l|lv|L}}{{l|lv|l}}, {{l|lv|Ļ}}{{l|lv|ļ}}, {{l|lv|M}}{{l|lv|m}}, {{l|lv|N}}{{l|lv|n}}, {{l|lv|Ņ}}{{l|lv|ņ}}, {{l|lv|O}}{{l|lv|o}}, {{l|lv|P}}{{l|lv|p}}, {{l|lv|R}}{{l|lv|r}}, {{l|lv|S}}{{l|lv|s}}, {{l|lv|Š}}{{l|lv|š}}, {{l|lv|T}}{{l|lv|t}}, {{l|lv|U}}{{l|lv|u}}, {{l|lv|Ū}}{{l|lv|ū}}, {{l|lv|V}}{{l|lv|v}}, {{l|lv|Z}}{{l|lv|z}}, {{l|lv|Ž}}{{l|lv|ž}}\n\n==Livonian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{qualifier|phoneme}} {{liv-IPA|ɡ}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|liv}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|liv|letter|11}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/liv}}\n\n==Lushootseed==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|lut|/ɡ/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|lut}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|lut|letter|12}}\n\n==Malay==\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|ms}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|ms|letter|7}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/ms}}\n\n==Maltese==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|mt|/ɡ/}}\n* {{IPA|mt|/k/}} {{q|per final devoicing or assimilation to a following voiceless obstruent}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|mt}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|mt|letter|8}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/mt}}\n\n==Navajo==\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|nv}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|nv|letter}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/nv}}\n\n==North Frisian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|frr|[ɡ]|q2=in the syllable [[coda]]|[ç]|[x]}}\n* {{IPA|frr|q1=at the start of a word or stressed syllable|[ɡ̊]|q2=otherwise|[ç]|[x]|a=Sylt}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|frr}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|frr|letter}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* Word-internal or final ⟨{{l|frr||g}}⟩ alternates with ⟨{{l|frr|c|ch}}⟩ in many cases. Originally this alternation reproduced closely the pronunciation: voiced {{IPAchar|[ʝ~ɣ]}} and devoiced {{IPAchar|[ç~x]}} respectively. For example, {{m|frr|[[kuuch]] ''>'' kuuger}} reflected {{IPAchar|[kuːx]}} > {{IPAchar|[kuːɣɐ]}}, whereas {{m|frr|[[fraag]] ''>'' fraagen}} reflected {{IPAchar|[fraːɣ]}} > {{IPAchar|[fraːɣn̩]}}. \n* Most contemporary dialects have eliminated the voiced fricatives {{IPAchar|[ʝ]}}, {{IPAchar|[ɣ]}} devoicing them to {{IPAchar|[ç]}}, {{IPAchar|[x]}} in coda and otherwise hardening them to {{IPAchar|[ɡ]}} (similarly to northern Standard German). This means that the pronunciation can still be deduced from the spelling, but it has become inscrutable why {{m|frr||kuuch}} has final ⟨{{l|frr||ch}}⟩ and {{m|frr||fraag}} does not, given that both of them are now pronounced with {{IPAchar|[x]}} in the singular and {{IPAchar|[ɡ]}} in the plural.\n* Sylt Frisian has also eliminated the voiced fricatives, but it has devoiced them to {{IPAchar|[ç]}}, {{IPAchar|[x]}} in all positions. Accordingly, it has not only {{m|frr|Fraag}} {{IPAchar|[froːx]}}, but also plural {{m|frr||Fraagen}} {{IPAchar|[froːxn̩]}}. With very few exceptions, ⟨{{l|frr||g}}⟩ is written after long or unstressed vowels and ⟨{{l|frr||ch}}⟩ after short stressed vowels.\n\n===See also===\n* {{sense|North Frisian letters}} {{l|frr|[[a]], [[ä]], [[å]], [[ā]], [[b]], [[c]], [[d]], [[đ]], [[e]], [[ē]], [[f]], [[g]], [[h]], [[i]], [[j]], [[k]], [[l]], [[m]], [[n]], [[o]], [[ö]], [[p]], [[r]], [[s]], [[t]], [[u]], [[ü]], [[v]], [[w]] ([[q]], [[x]], [[y]], [[z]])}}\n\n==Norwegian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{sense|letter name}} {{IPA|no|/ɡeː/}}\n* {{sense|phoneme}} {{IPA|no|/ɡ/|/k/|/j/|/ʃ/|/ɪ/}}\n* {{audio|nb|LL-Q9043 (nor)-Jon Harald Søby (WMNO)-g.wav}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|no}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|no|letter|7}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* When g is written before j, they merge together and create the sound of y in '''you'''.\n* G is sometimes pronounced like the s in '''sugar''' in words of French origin, like '''genre''', due to the fact that Norwegian lacks the voiced palato-alveolar sibilant [ʒ].\n* In eastern and nothern dialects, g at the end of pronouns is pronounced like the y in '''boy'''. In western and southern dialects, the g is pronounced like g in '''great'''.\n* When g is written before t, it is pronounced like the k in '''king'''.\n* In Norwegian runic inscriptions from 17-19 centuries this letter is usually written as [[ᚵ]].\n\n==Nupe==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{sense|phoneme}} {{IPA|nup|/ɡ/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|nup}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|nup|letter|8}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/nup}}\n\n==O'odham==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|ood|heg||full form}}\n\n===Etymology===\nShorterning of {{m|ood|heg}}, itself from {{m|ood|hegai}}.\n\n===Article===\n{{head|ood|article}}\n\n# [[the]], [[a]] {{gloss|determiner}}\n#: {{ux|ood|Gakoḍk 'o '''g''' huk.|'''The''' board is warped.}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:ood:Mathiot:2013|I|page=223–4}}\n* {{R:ood:Saxton:1998|g/heg|page=13}}\n* {{R:ood:Zepeda:1983|page=158}}\n\n==Polish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{pl-ety-letter}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pl-pr|gie|h=-|r=-|a=LL-Q809 (pol)-Olaf-g.wav}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|pl}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|pl|letter|10|gie}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/pl}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n[[File:G is for Gatto.jpg|thumb|250px|upright|The word for ''cat'' in Portuguese is ''gato'', and starts with g.]]\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{q|letter name}} {{IPA|pt|/ˈʒe/|a=BR}}\n* {{audio|pt|Pt-br-g.ogg|a=BR}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|pt}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|pt|letter|7}}\n#* {{RQ:mul:Rowling Harry Potter|pt-BR|5|page=75|text=Não o perdoou por abandonar o serviço em vez de se'''g'''uir você.|t=She didn't forgive him for abandoning his service instead of following you.}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/pt}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pt:Aulete}}\n* {{R:pt:Priberam}}\n\n==Romani==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|rom|/ɡ/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|rom}}\n\n# {{lb|rom|International Standard}} {{Latn-def|rom|letter|9}}\n# {{lb|rom|Pan-Vlax}} {{Latn-def|rom|letter|10}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/rom}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ro|/ɡ/|/dʒ/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|ro}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|ro|letter|9|ge|ghe|gî}}\n\n====Usage notes====\nSee {{m|ro|G}} for pronunciation notes.\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/ro}}\n\n==Scottish Gaelic==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|gd|/k/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|gd}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|gd|letter|7|prec=f|foll=h|addl=; traditionally named {{l|gd|gort|t=ivy}}}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/gd}}\n\n==Serbo-Croatian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{qualifier|phoneme}} {{IPA|sh|/ɡ/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|sh|Cyrl:г}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|sh|letter|11|alphvar={{l|sh|gajica}}|prec=f|foll=h}}\n\n==Silesian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{szl-ety-letter}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|szl}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|szl|letter|9}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/szl}}\n\n==Skolt Sami==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{qualifier|phoneme}} {{IPA|sms|/ɡ/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|sms}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|sms|letter|12}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/sms}}\n\n==Slovak==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{sk-IPA}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|sk}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|sk|letter|11}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* Used only in loanwords.\n\n===See also===\n{{list:Latin script letters/sk}}\n\n==Slovene==\n{{wp|sl:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom Gaj's Latin alphabet {{m|sh|g}}, from {{der|sl|cs|-}} alphabet {{m|cs|g}}, from Latin {{m|la|g}}. Pronunciation as {{IPAchar|/ɡə/}} is initial Slovene (phoneme plus a fill vowel) and the second pronunciation is probably taken from {{der|sl|de|g}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* Phoneme\n{{sl-pronounce\n|IPAt={{IPA|sl|/ɡ/|[k]}}\n|SNPTt={{SNPT|/g/|[k]}}\n|IPAnt={{IPA|sl|/ɡ/|[k]}}\n|SNPTnt={{SNPT|/g/|[k]}}\n|IPAg={{IPA|sl|/ɣ/|[x]}}\n|SNPTg={{SNPT|/ɣ/|[h]}}\n|IPAcoll={{IPA|sl|/ɡ/|[k]|[x]}}\n|SNPTcoll={{SNPT|/g/|[k]|[h]}}\n}}\n\n* Letter name\n{{sl-pronounce\n|nt=g\n|phonetic=gə̀, gé\n|tonal=ə̏, ẹ̄\n|IPAt={{IPA|sl|[ˈɡə̂]|[ˈɡêː]|[ˈɡěː]}}\n|SNPTt={{SNPT|[gə̏]|[gẹ̄]}}\n|IPAnt={{IPA|sl|[ˈɡə]|[ˈɡeː]}}\n|SNPTnt={{SNPT|[gə̀]|[gé]}}\n|audiont={{audio|sl|Sl-nt-g.ogg}}\n|IPAg={{IPA|sl|[ˈɣə̂]|[ˈɣêː]|[ˈɣěː]}}\n|SNPTg={{SNPT|[ɣə̏]|[ɣẹ̄]}}\n|audiog={{audio|sl|Sl-nt-g-dialectal.ogg}}\n}}\n{{sl-pronounce-other\n|rhymes={{rhymes|sl|ə|eː}}\n|rhymesSNPT={{SNPTchar|ə̀|é}}\n|hyphenation={{hyphenation|sl|g}}\n|homophonest={{homophones|sl|G}}\n|homophonesnt={{homophones|sl|G}}\n|alp=*gə̀\n|car=*gə̏\n|vk=*gə̏\n|si=*gə̏\n|lc=*gə̏\n|uc=*gə̏\n|ss=*gə̏\n|ns=*gə̏\n|pan=*gə̏\n}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|sl}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|sl|letter|8}}\n# {{Latn-def|sl|letter|11|alphvar=Resian}}\n# {{Latn-def|sl|letter|8|alphvar=Natisone Valley dialect}}\n\n===Symbol===\n{{head|sl|symbol}}\n\n# {{qualifier|[[wikipedia:Slovene_national_phonetic_transcription|SNPT]]}} ''[[phonetic|Phonetic]] [[transcription]] of sound'' [{{IPAlink|ɡ}}].\n\n===Noun===\n{{sl-noun|g|m-in}}\n\n# {{ng|The name of the [[Appendix:Latin script|Latin script]] letter '''''[[G]]''''' / '''''[[g]]'''''.}}\n# {{lb|sl|linguistics}} {{ng|The name of the [[phoneme]] ''/{{IPAlink|ɡ}}/''.}}\n\n====Declension====\n* Overall more common\n{{sl-decl-noun-table3|g|g-ja|[[g-ju]], ''[[g-ji]]''|g|[[g-ju]], ''[[g-ji]]''|g-jem|g|g-ja|g-jev|g-jema|g-ja|g-jih|g-jema|g-ja|g-ji|g-jev|g-jem|g-je|g-jih|g-ji|g-ji|decl=m-in-1-s|infix=j-|accent=1}}\n\n* More common when with a definite adjective\n{{sl-decl-noun-table3|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|g|decl=m-3|accent=1}}\n\n* Dialectal, in common written language used till 19th century\n{{sl-decl-noun-table3|g|g-ja|[[g-ju]], ''[[g-ji]]''|g|[[g-ju]], ''[[g-ji]]''|g-jom|g|g-ja|g-jov|g-joma|g-ja|g-jih|g-joma|g-ja|g-ji|g-jov|g-jom|g-je|g-jih|g-ji|g-ji|decl=m-in-1|infix=j-}}\n\n===Derived terms===\n{{col4|sl|ǧ|ǵ|ǥ}}\n\n===See also===\n{{list:Latin script letters/sl/simple}}\n* {{l|sl|ǧ}}\n* {{l|sl|ǵ}}\n* {{l|sl|ǥ}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:sl:Fran}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|raw:/ɡ/<q:phoneme>,raw:[ɣ̞],raw:/x/|gé<q:letter name><audio:letter g es es.flac<a:Spain>>}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|es}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|es|letter|7}}\n\n===See also===\n{{list:Latin script letters/es}}\n\n==Swedish==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n; Letter name\n* {{IPA|sv|/ɡeː/}}\n\n; Phoneme\n* {{IPA|sv|/ɡ/|/j/|/ɧ/}}\n** {{homophones|sv|j|qq1=in some positions}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|sv}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|sv|letter|7|ge}} Pronounced {{IPAchar|/ɡ/}} in front of ''a'', ''o'', ''u'' and ''å'' and {{IPAchar|/j/}} in front of ''e'', ''i'', ''y'', ''ä'' and ''ö''. Pronounced {{IPAchar|/ɧ/}} in some loan words.\n\n==Tagalog==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{bor+|tl|es|g}}. Each pronunciation has a different source:\n* Filipino alphabet pronunciation is influenced by {{der|tl|en|g}}.\n* Abakada alphabet pronunciation is influenced by Baybayin character {{m|tl|ᜄ|tr=ga}}.\n* Abecedario pronunciation is from {{der|tl|es|g}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n{{tl-pr\n|dyí<qq:letter name, Filipino alphabet>\n|gá<qq:letter name, Abakada alphabet>\n|hé<qq:letter name, Abecedario>\n|+<qq:phoneme>\n|raw:/ɡ/ [ɣ]<qq:phoneme, intervocalic>\n|j<qq:phoneme, followed by e or i, English unadapted loanwords>\n|h<qq:phoneme, followed by e or i, Spanish unadapted loanwords>\n|s<qq:phoneme, followed by e or i, Spanish unadapted loanwords, obsolete>\n}}\n\n====Letter====\n{{letter|tl}}\n\n# {{tl-letter def|7|dyi|alph=fil}}\n# {{tl-letter def|6|ga|alph=abak}}\n# {{lb|tl|historical}} {{tl-letter def|8|ge|alph=abec}}\n\n=====See also=====\n{{list:Latin script letters/tl}}\n* {{l|tl|g̃}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n\n====Interjection====\n{{tl-head|interjection}}\n\n# {{lb|tl|slang}} {{alt case|tl|G}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:Pambansang Diksiyonaryo}}\n\n==Tlingit==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|tli|/k/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|tli}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|tli|letter}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/tli}}\n\n==Turkish==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{sense|phoneme}} {{IPA|tr|/ɡ/|/ɟ/}}\n* {{sense|letter name}} {{IPA|tr|/ɟeː/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|tr}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|tr|letter|8|ge}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/tr}}\n\n==Turkmen==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{qualifier|phoneme}} {{IPA|tk|/ɡ~ʁ/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|tk}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|tk|letter|8|ge}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/tk}}\n\n==Vietnamese==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{vi-IPA|giê|gờ|gờ đơn}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|vi}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|vi|letter|10}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/vi}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|vi|noun}}\n\n# {{contraction of|vi|-ương}}\n#: {{ux|vi|lương → l'''g'''|work pay}}\n\n==Welsh==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|cy|/ɛɡ/|a=standard}}\n** {{IPA|cy|/ɡə/|a=informal}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|cy}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|cy|letter|10|èg|prec=ff|foll=ng}}\n\n===See also===\n{{list:Latin script letters/cy}}\n\n===Mutation===\n* G at the beginning of words is omitted in a {{l|en|soft mutation}}, mutates to {{l|cy|Ng}} in a {{l|en|nasal mutation}} and is unchanged by {{l|en|aspirate mutation}}, for example with the word {{m|cy|gorsaf||station}}:\n{{cy-mut|gorsaf}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:cy:GPC}}\n\n==Yoruba==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{sense|phoneme}} {{IPA|yo|/ɡ/}}\n* {{sense|letter name}} {{IPA|yo|/ɡí/}}\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|yo}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|yo|letter|7|gí}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/yo}}\n\n==Zulu==\n\n===Letter===\n{{letter|zu}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|zu|letter|7}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letters/zu}}"}}